Interview Question Answer

Q: Why did you choose VARMA instead of VARMAX?

Answer:

The available Infosys dataset contained only endogenous variables such as Open Price, High Price, Low Price, Close Price, 
and Traded Quantity. Since no external explanatory variables were available, 
VARMA was selected to model the interdependencies among multiple stock variables.
VARMAX would be appropriate when external factors such as market indices, exchange rates, or economic indicators are included.

